title: Const generic default ICE: The type checker should prevent reading from a never-written local

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Const generic defaults are being stabilized, https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/90207/. But I found an issue that occured earlier in the length expressions of arrays, see https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/72115 ### Code ```Rust struct X; ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0-nightly (4e8fb743c 2022-02-03) ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_const_eval/src/interpret/eval_context.rs:202:17: The type checker should prevent reading from a never-written local ```
